Self-Supporting Towers: G-Series 









ROHN Self-supporting G-Series towers offer an easy, low-cost solution to get light weight self supporting antenna towers in the air quickly. By using the G-Series tower as a self-supporting tower, you minimize land area usage.
 
ROHN tower manufacturing Self-Supporting G-Series towers are functional in a wide variety of wind speeds, with and without ice.
 
See ROHN's Self-Supporting G-Series Information to help identify the right structure for your project. Theses are the same sturdy, robust self-supporting antenna towers that ROHN tower manufacturing has fabricated for years. Each larger model allows for more loading capacity.
